Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of computer vision analysis in the field of art history, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The examination of the ethical consequences of this technology and the challenge to the authority of the art expert suggest a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper may touch on issues related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) in terms of protecting the authenticity of artwork.
